.Dd July 3, 2026
.Dt BPM 1
.Os Blueberry Linux
.Sh NAME
.Nm bpm
.Nd Blueberry package manager
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar command
.Op Ar arguments ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the native package manager for Blueberry Linux. It installs
.Pa .bpm
packages from an HTTP(S) mirror, verifying an ed25519-signed index and a
per-package SHA-256 before anything is written to disk. Downloaded packages are
kept in a local cache so they can be reinstalled, rolled back, or downgraded
offline.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm install Ar name|file ...
Install one or more packages, resolving dependencies from the repositories. A
local
.Pa .bpm
or
.Pa .pkg.tar.zst
file may be given directly.
.It Cm remove Ar name ...
Remove installed package(s). Refuses to strand a still-required package unless
.Fl f
is given.
.It Cm autoremove
Remove dependencies that are no longer required by any explicitly-installed
package.
.It Cm update
Sync the repository indices (fetch and verify the signed
.Pa bpm.index ) .
.It Cm upgrade
Upgrade every installed package to the newest available version. The kernel is a
pinned artifact and is not part of this.
.It Cm rollback Ar name
Reinstall the previous cached version of a package (the newest cached version
older than the one installed).
.It Cm downgrade Ar name Ns Op = Ns Ar version
Install a specific older cached version, or the previous version when no
.Ar version
is given.
.It Cm search Ar term
Search the repository index by name and description.
.It Cm list
List installed packages and their versions.
.It Cm info Ar name
Show a package's metadata (installed record, else the repo entry).
.It Cm why Ar name
Explain why a package is present: which installed packages require it and
whether it was installed explicitly.
.It Cm depends Ar name
Print a package's dependency tree.
.It Cm files Ar name
List the files a package owns.
.It Cm owns Ar path
Report which package owns a path.
.It Cm clean Op Fl -all
Prune the download cache. By default the two newest versions of each package are
kept (so
.Cm rollback
and
.Cm downgrade
still work);
.Fl -all
empties the cache.
.El
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl f , Fl -force
Skip the disk-space, file-conflict, and reverse-dependency checks.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev BPM_ROOT
Install into the given directory instead of
.Pa / .
Scriptlets and
.Xr ldconfig 8
are run chrooted into that root.
.It Ev BPM_ALLOW_UNSIGNED
Accept an index whose ed25519 signature is missing or invalid. Insecure; for
development only.
.It Ev BPM_NO_SCRIPTLETS
Skip pre/post-install scriptlets and service enablement.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa /var/lib/bpm/db
Installed-package database.
.It Pa /var/lib/bpm/cache
Downloaded package cache (source for rollback/downgrade).
.It Pa /var/lib/bpm/index
The synced, verified repository index.
.It Pa /etc/bpm/repos.conf
Repository/mirror list.
.It Pa /etc/bpm/provided
Names the base image already provides; treated as satisfied dependencies.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr makewhatis 8
.Pp
After each transaction
.Nm
rebuilds the man-page index so newly installed pages are found by
.Xr man 1
and
.Xr apropos 1 .
